thread.title: UW volleyball sweeps Cal
thread.title_full: UW volleyball sweeps Cal | The Seattle Times

author: Seattle Times staff
title: UW volleyball sweeps Cal
text:
The Washington volleyball team beat California in Berkeley for the fourth consecutive season, doing so in straight sets Friday.
Senior Lianna Sybeldon and sophomore Tia Scambray combined for 19 kills with just one error between them on 30 swings as the fourth-ranked Huskies wrapped up the first half of Pac-12 play with the 25-15, 30-28, 25-16 win.
Washington saved six set points in the second set and hit .388 for the night, compared to .121 for the Bears. The Huskies (18-2, 8-2) also had nine blocks to one for California (7-13, 1-8).
Washington hosts league-leading USC next Friday, the only remaining undefeated team in the country.

Sybeldon wrapped up a phenomenal week, hitting over .700 in both matches, and raising her NCAA-leading attack percentage to .502 for the year.
Scambray posted nine kills on 18 swings without a miss for a .500 percentage. Courtney Schwan also had her best match since returning from a foot injury, as she had seven kills and hit .417.
Volleyball McKenna Woodford had a career-high 18 kills but Washington State (14-7, 3-6 Pac-12) fell at No. 11 Stanford (13-5, 7-3) 25-20, 25-20, 25-19.
Men’s soccer No. 17 Washington (6-3-5) dropped its final nonconference match of the season, losing at No. 20 Maryland 1-0. Maryland outshot the Huskies 24-7, but a UW own goal was the only score.
• No. 19 Seattle University (13-3, 6-1) earned a 3-2 victory at reigning Western Athletic Conference champion UNLV (9-4-1, 3-2-1). Alex Roldan scored the Redhawks’ first goal, Sam Langston got the equalizer on a penalty kick in the 60th minute and Kyle Bjornethun got the game-winner in the 87th minute.
• Rocky Mountain College beat host Northwest University 2-1.
Women’s soccer Sarah Shimer’s first career shutout and Kimby Keever’s game-winning goal in the 87th minute gave the Huskies a 1-0 win over No. 14 Cal at Husky Soccer Field, ending the Bears’ five-game winning streak. The Huskies (11-3-2, 4-2-1 Pac-12) are 7-1 at home this season.
• Seattle U (11-2-3, 6-0-2 WAC) defeated host CSU Bakersfield 2-0. Julia Moravec scored in the 37th minute and Hunter Mar added a goal in the 68th minute.
• Kortney Hudak and Gabriela De Andrade scored goals as host Northwest U beat Rocky Mountain College 2-0.
Swimming The Seattle University women split a double-dual meet in Goodyear, Ariz., defeating Loyola Marymount 109-96 but losing to host Grand Canyon 120-84. Blaise Wittenauer-Lee had two individual victories for the Redhawks (400IM, 4:26.90; 100 breast, 1:04.49).
• Jack Baldoni (100 fly, 51.25) and Austin Barnard (1,000 free, 10:02.24) picked up event victories but the Seattle U men lost to Grand Canyon 136-68 in Goodyear, Ariz.
• The Washington State women defeated UNLV 185.5-108.5 and lost to host Arizona 182-98. Elise Locke won the 200 fly (2:01.82) and the 100 fly (55.81).
Men’s basketball Dak Shagren scored 24 points and newcomer Ben Tuckovic had 21 as host Northwest University opened its season with an 81-62 victory over Vancouver Island.
Men’s golf The professional team beat the amateur team with a two-day point total of 12 to 8 in the 67th Hudson Cup matches at Broadmoor GC. In the 24th edition of the Senior Hudson Cup, the professionals beat the amateurs 13 to 7.
From sports-information reports.
